Regarding that matter, Martina Kemrová pointed out: “The competitive environment of the mobile market was recently amplified by the entry of the fourth mobile operator into the market.
The character of the Czech Republic mobile market is clearly evidenced that the introduction of another player would place higher demands on it and above all on its services.
The lack of interest by the Czech regulatory bodies is almost astonishing.
This means not only the attitude of the CTO, which unfortunately in Czechia - unlike in Great Britain and other developed countries - has no authority to intervene in economic competition.
This authority belongs to the Office for the Protection of Competition (OPC) exclusively.
