Making effective appeals to Hispanic voters is a tricky business.
Obama's education proposals are a case in point.
The Obama campaign says that, "African-American and Latino students are significantly less likely to graduate than white students," which is true.
The Obama education plan specifically advocates transitional bilingual education for English-learning.
The question for Mr Obama is whether his commitment to bilingual education, which emphasizes classroom instruction in other languages, overrides his interest in achievement gaps.
Take, for example, Sixth Street Prep, a charter elementary school in southern Los Angeles County.
The school's students are mostly Hispanic and low income.
